# Superpowers Skills

Before starting any task, check if a superpowers skill applies. If there's even a small chance one fits, read and follow it before doing anything else — including asking clarifying questions.

Skills live in `~/.cursor/skills/superpowers/` and are listed in your agent_skills. Read the SKILL.md file before using.

## When to invoke which skill

| Trigger | Skill |
|---------|-------|
| Any creative work: new feature, component, behavior change | `brainstorming` |
| You have a spec or requirements for a multi-step task | `writing-plans` |
| Executing a written implementation plan | `executing-plans` |
| 2+ independent tasks that can be parallelized | `dispatching-parallel-agents` or `subagent-driven-development` |
| Bug, test failure, or unexpected behavior | `systematic-debugging` |
| Implementing any feature or bugfix | `test-driven-development` |
| About to claim work is done, fixed, or passing | `verification-before-completion` |
| Completing a feature or before merging | `requesting-code-review` |
| Received code review feedback | `receiving-code-review` |
| Implementation complete, deciding how to integrate | `finishing-a-development-branch` |
| Need isolation from current workspace | `using-git-worktrees` |

## Priority order

1. **Process skills first** (brainstorming, debugging) — these determine the approach
2. **Implementation skills second** — these guide execution
